{
  "name": "GitHub PR Workflow",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Local GitHub AI Code Reviewer\n**What this workflow does:**\nWhen a Pull Request is opened or updated, it fetches the full code diff, sends it to your local Ollama instance for expert analysis, and posts the structured review as a comment directly on the PR thread.\n\n**Trigger Events:** PR `opened` + `synchronize`\n\n**Execution Flow:**\n`GitHub Webhook` → `Filter Action` → `Fetch PR Files` → `Format Diff` → `Ollama Review Agent` → `Post Comment`\n\n**Before activating:** Follow the orange Webhook Setup note and add your GitHub PAT.",
        "height": 300,
        "width": 440,
        "color": 7
      },
      "id": "136542df-1487-495f-9b80-2f8da9fab150",
      "name": "Workflow Overview",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [0, 0]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### GitHub Webhook Configuration\n1. Go to your repo → **Settings → Webhooks → Add webhook**\n2. **Payload URL:** Copy the *Production URL* from the webhook node\n3. **Content type:** `application/json`\n4. **Which events?** → Select individual events → ✅ **Pull requests**\n\n> ℹ️ Only `opened` and `synchronize` actions are processed.",
        "height": 240,
        "width": 400,
        "color": 3
      },
      "id": "288863f5-6484-451d-b959-dc6e23d8a1a1",
      "name": "Webhook Setup Guide",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [464, 0]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### Required Credentials\n**1. GitHub Personal Access Token**\n→ Replace `placeholder_github_pat` in:\n  - *Fetch PR Files from GitHub*\n  - *Post Review Comment on PR*\n\n**2. Local Ollama Server**\n→ Make sure Ollama is running in your Terminal with:\n`OLLAMA_HOST=0.0.0.0 ollama serve`",
        "height": 240,
        "width": 400,
        "color": 5
      },
      "id": "9dd38ccb-2faf-44ae-bf98-1a7b5a2a5294",
      "name": "Credentials Guide",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [912, 0]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "httpMethod": "POST",
        "path": "github-pr-review",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "023cf65a-9b6e-4416-859b-baf055481fd3",
      "name": "GitHub PR Webhook",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.webhook",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [208, 512],
      "webhookId": "pr-review-wh-001"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "options": {
            "caseSensitive": true,
            "leftValue": "",
            "typeValidation": "strict",
            "version": 1
          },
          "conditions": [
            {
              "id": "cond-opened",
              "leftValue": "={{ $json.body.action }}",
              "rightValue": "opened",
              "operator": {
                "type": "string",
                "operation": "equals"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "cond-synchronize",
              "leftValue": "={{ $json.body.action }}",
              "rightValue": "synchronize",
              "operator": {
                "type": "string",
                "operation": "equals"
              }
            }
          ],
          "combinator": "or"
        },
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "bf0b43e7-f5d1-4aeb-9e7d-b014e1034ea7",
      "name": "Filter: PR Opened or Updated",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [448, 512]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "url": "=https://api.github.com/repos/{{ $json.body.repository.full_name }}/pulls/{{ $json.body.number }}/files?per_page=100",
        "authentication": "predefinedCredentialType",
        "nodeCredentialType": "githubApi",
        "sendHeaders": true,
        "headerParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            {
              "name": "Authorization",
              "value": "Bearer placeholder_github_pat"
            },
            {
              "name": "Accept",
              "value": "application/vnd.github+json"
            },
            {
              "name": "X-GitHub-Api-Version",
              "value": "2022-11-28"
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {
          "response": {
            "response": {
              "neverError": true
            }
          }
        }
      },
      "id": "6f844c97-7986-4bb3-b7f2-eba5ce9dd399",
      "name": "Fetch PR Files from GitHub",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4.2,
      "position": [688, 368],
      "credentials": {
        "githubApi": {
          "id": "FWnRSNWcE4udURMM",
          "name": "GitHub account"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "3c15bee7-ca72-4416-a82a-394f3dde3cdc",
      "name": "Event Ignored",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.set",
      "typeVersion": 3.4,
      "position": [688, 672]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const allItems = $input.all();\nconst webhookBody = $('GitHub PR Webhook').first().json.body;\nconst pr = webhookBody.pull_request;\nconst repo = webhookBody.repository;\n\nlet files = [];\nconst firstJson = allItems[0]?.json;\n\nif (Array.isArray(firstJson)) {\n  files = firstJson;\n} else if (allItems.length > 1) {\n  files = allItems.map(i => i.json);\n} else if (firstJson && 'filename' in firstJson) {\n  files = [firstJson];\n}\n\nlet diffContent = '## Pull Request: ' + (pr?.title || 'N/A') + '\\n';\ndiffContent += '**Repo:** ' + repo.full_name + ' | **PR #' + webhookBody.number + '**\\n\\n';\n\nfor (const file of files) {\n  diffContent += '#### File: ' + file.filename + '\\n';\n  if (file.patch) {\n    diffContent += '```diff\\n' + file.patch + '\\n```\\n\\n';\n  }\n}\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    diffContent,\n    prNumber: webhookBody.number,\n    commentsApiUrl: 'https://api.github.com/repos/' + repo.full_name + '/issues/' + webhookBody.number + '/comments'\n  }\n}];"
      },
      "id": "5aafe156-4c2f-4df2-8112-57c1b72c3aeb",
      "name": "Format Diff for Ollama",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [928, 368]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "={{ $json.diffContent }}",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "21455f58-e5f1-4b04-85e7-0472fbee89e7",
      "name": "Ollama Review Agent",
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 1.6,
      "position": [1152, 368]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "method": "POST",
        "url": "={{ $('Format Diff for Ollama').item.json.commentsApiUrl }}",
        "authentication": "predefinedCredentialType",
        "nodeCredentialType": "githubApi",
        "sendHeaders": true,
        "headerParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            {
              "name": "Authorization",
              "value": "Bearer placeholder_github_pat"
            },
            {
              "name": "Accept",
              "value": "application/vnd.github+json"
            },
            {
              "name": "X-GitHub-Api-Version",
              "value": "2022-11-28"
            }
          ]
        },
        "sendBody": true,
        "contentType": "raw",
        "rawContentType": "application/json",
        "body": "={{ JSON.stringify({ body: '### Local AI Code Review\\n\\n' + $json.output }) }}",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "815dd118-4c17-479a-874d-e6ba6ff62be5",
      "name": "Post Review Comment on PR",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4.2,
      "position": [1424, 368],
      "credentials": {
        "githubApi": {
          "id": "FWnRSNWcE4udURMM",
          "name": "GitHub account"
        }
      }
    },
